A NOTE ON CSS CLASS NAMES
-------------------------

angulux deliberately keeps the `p-*` CSS class names inherited from PrimeNG 21.1.9.
This is a compatibility decision, not a branding one: it is what allows themes built
for the MIT releases of @primeuix/themes to keep working, and it gives projects
migrating from PrimeNG 21 a path that does not require restyling everything.

Element and attribute selectors are NOT inherited — those were renamed to `agl-*`
and `agl*` respectively.
